decision_details:
- the proposal made by Hon. Basil Rajapaksa, Minister of Economic Affairs to establish a Tourism Authority and to prepare a Bill for the purpose to be presented in Parliament, was approved by the Cabinet.  The salient features of the Bill are as follows:

*	develop Sri Lanka as a quality tourist and travel destination and a gateway to the South Asian Region;

*	encourage persons or bodies of persons in the private sector to participate in the promotion of Tourism Industry and Training Activities connected with such industry;  

*	promote Sri Lanka as a venue for international, regional and domestic conventions, meetings and exhibitions; and

*	promote and improve services and facilities provided for tourists
